types.name: RateDataV1Params
docs: @notice struct to set borrow rate data for version 1

fields.name: kink
docs: @param kink in borrow rate. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_zero
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationZero desired borrow rate when utilization is zero. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
i.e. constant minimum borrow rate
e.g. at utilization = 0.01% rate could still be at least 4% (rateAtUtilizationZero would be 400 then)

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_kink
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationKink borrow rate when utilization is at kink. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
e.g. when rate should be 7% at kink then rateAtUtilizationKink would be 700

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_max
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationMax borrow rate when utilization is maximum at 100%. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
e.g. when rate should be 125% at 100% then rateAtUtilizationMax would be 12_500

types.name: RateDataV2Params
docs: @notice struct to set borrow rate data for version 2

fields.name: kink1
docs: @param kink1 first kink in borrow rate. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
utilization below kink 1 usually means slow increase in rate, once utilization is above kink 1 borrow rate increases faster

fields.name: kink2
docs: @param kink2 second kink in borrow rate. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
utilization below kink 2 usually means slow / medium increase in rate, once utilization is above kink 2 borrow rate increases fast

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_zero
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationZero desired borrow rate when utilization is zero. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
i.e. constant minimum borrow rate
e.g. at utilization = 0.01% rate could still be at least 4% (rateAtUtilizationZero would be 400 then)

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_kink1
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationKink1 desired borrow rate when utilization is at first kink. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
e.g. when rate should be 7% at first kink then rateAtUtilizationKink would be 700

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_kink2
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationKink2 desired borrow rate when utilization is at second kink. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
e.g. when rate should be 7% at second kink then rateAtUtilizationKink would be 1_200

fields.name: rate_at_utilization_max
docs: @param rateAtUtilizationMax desired borrow rate when utilization is maximum at 100%. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
e.g. when rate should be 125% at 100% then rateAtUtilizationMax would be 12_500

types.name: RateModel
docs: Interest rate model data

types.name: TokenConfig
docs: @notice struct to set token config

fields.name: token
docs: @param token address

fields.name: fee
docs: @param fee charges on borrower's interest. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100

fields.name: max_utilization
docs: @param maxUtilization maximum allowed utilization. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
set to 100% to disable and have default limit of 100% (avoiding SLOAD).

types.name: TokenReserve
docs: Token configuration and exchange prices

types.name: UserBorrowConfig
docs: @notice struct to set user borrow & payback config

fields.name: mode
docs: @param mode: 0 = without interest. 1 = with interest

fields.name: expand_percent
docs: @param expandPercent debt limit expand percent. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
Also used to calculate rate at which debt limit should decrease (instant).

fields.name: expand_duration
docs: @param expandDuration debt limit expand duration in seconds.
used to calculate rate together with expandPercent

fields.name: base_debt_ceiling
docs: @param baseDebtCeiling base borrow limit. until here, borrow limit remains as baseDebtCeiling
(user can borrow until this point at once without stepped expansion). Above this, automated limit comes in place.
amount in raw (to be multiplied with exchange price) or normal depends on configured mode in user config for the token:
with interest -> raw, without interest -> normal

fields.name: max_debt_ceiling
docs: @param maxDebtCeiling max borrow ceiling, maximum amount the user can borrow.
amount in raw (to be multiplied with exchange price) or normal depends on configured mode in user config for the token:
with interest -> raw, without interest -> normal

types.name: UserBorrowPosition
docs: User borrow position

types.name: UserSupplyConfig
docs: @notice struct to set user supply & withdrawal config

fields.name: mode
docs: @param mode: 0 = without interest. 1 = with interest

fields.name: expand_percent
docs: @param expandPercent withdrawal limit expand percent. in 1e2: 100% = 10_000; 1% = 100
Also used to calculate rate at which withdrawal limit should decrease (instant).

fields.name: expand_duration
docs: @param expandDuration withdrawal limit expand duration in seconds.
used to calculate rate together with expandPercent

fields.name: base_withdrawal_limit
docs: @param baseWithdrawalLimit base limit, below this, user can withdraw the entire amount.
amount in raw (to be multiplied with exchange price) or normal depends on configured mode in user config for the token:
with interest -> raw, without interest -> normal

types.name: UserSupplyPosition
docs: User supply position
